parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jerk, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips between gears
grinding noise
vehicle loses power
stalls
or jerks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brakes quit working
hard to stop
vehicle stalls
or sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduction of engine power can cause the vehicle to lose speed, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine power is reduced
vehicle surges up and down
or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
or the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vacuum pump can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brakes are hard to stop
or sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vacuum pump can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard to press
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the "Service Brake Assist" message appears on the dashboard
the brake assist warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard to press
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the "Service Brake Assist" message appears on the dashboard
the brake assist warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard to press
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the "Low Brake Fluid" message appears on the dashboard
the brake warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to start
error messages appear on the dashboard
the battery is severely depleted
and the vehicle's systems (e.g.
steering
windows
doors) are inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The volume adjusts itself
the system starts blaring loudly
and it continuously turns on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear vision system can cause accidents or injuries when reversing, especially when there are pedestrians or objects behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The backup camera displays a blue screen with a "Service Rear Vision System" message
and the system is inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal gets stiff
the brakes lock up
and the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause accidents or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel jerks forcefully to one side
and the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The computer/software glitch can cause various system failures, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's systems (e.g.
ESC
brake assist
airbags) malfunction
and error messages appear on the dashboard.
